    "updated_at": "2017-01-27T16:25:09Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The backoff you have set only applies when the channel is initially connecting to the server. In the case where you knock off one of the servers, the connection is still there. The client must attempt (and fail) to send a message to the shutdown server before realizing that it should reconnect to the second, healthy server.\r\n\r\nThe good news is that gRPC retries is an ongoing project, so that functionality should be available in a few months."
  },
